/*****************************************************************************
    Pending issues
*****************************************************************************/
Some operators like +% which fires addAttribute require its arguments to be fields (GroupItems). Other operators like genFor have a similar issue. Cannot feed such operators w/fields declared as local with only a type (like int someField). Well in incant you can.
Looking forward to JIT (and to a lesser extent w/C++ generation), incant needs to guarantee type matches for target and argument. ICO int + number would need to generate int + (int)number for example. For JIT, will need to emit the cast as a separate instruction. If there is no type match, throw an error. This is a generator issue (interpreter already handles type mismatches), but if we come up with a good argument matching approach it might help the interpreter too. Come to feel that typing is evil and incant does fine without it.
When generating an action not part of a class, no .h file generated. Generate .h when class containing actions is generated???
                                                                                
